description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Long Term Placement Opportunity Available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse – Nurse Team Manager Mental Health&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a Registered Mental Health Team Manager seeking a placement? Do you want to make a difference to patients quality of life?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a unique and exciting opportunity within&lt;strong&gt;Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;which will allow the successful candidate to gain&lt;strong&gt;regular shifts&lt;/strong&gt;and valuable&lt;strong&gt;experience&lt;/strong&gt;within a unique&lt;strong&gt;mental health&lt;/strong&gt;environment. We have a l&lt;strong&gt;ong term placement opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;available within Cannon House, providing you with the chance to work&lt;strong&gt;regular shifts&lt;/strong&gt;for a&lt;strong&gt;guaranteed period of 3 months on a rolling contract&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Cannon House, Southampton&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day Rate - £20.91 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Night/Sat Rate - £27.19 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sun/Bank Holiday Rate - £33.46 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals, is working in conjunction with Southern Health NHS Foundation trust who are seeking qualified Registered Mental Health Team Manager to join the bank working at Cannon House. NHS Professionals works in partnership with Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust to provide their temporary staffing requirements. We are seeking Registered Team Mangers to work 37.5 hours a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking Registered Team Managers to work at Canonn House based in Southampton, the team offers a range of treatments and therapies to support recovery with access to Early Intervention in Psychosis (EIP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be offered a full induction, training and development opportunities and a fully flexible approach to hours – full or part time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for a post you&lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have a minimum of 6 months experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;in a similar role held within the last 2 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have good communication skills and demonstrate evidence of team working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to take direction and instruction and be honest and trustworthy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive, weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHSP Stakeholder Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid annual leave and statutory maternity pay (subject to qualifying criteria)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First refusal on available shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information or an informal discussion, please contact The Southern Health Bank Team on: SHFTRecruitment@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be contacted via email throughout the recruitment process, so we urge you to ensure your email address submitted is accurate and checked regularly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration with NHS Professionals is subject to employment history and reference checking and offers of registration are therefore conditional upon the receipt of satisfactory references&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
